                <note rend="inline" type="source">890h.01/12: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dawes</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-04-16T16:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 16, 1931—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>97. Your 109, April 15, 4 p.m. There is no objection to you receiving the Afghan
                    Minister at his request. If he raises the question of recognition you should
                    state that you are not authorized to discuss the matter with him but that you
                    will be pleased to transmit to the Department any statement which his Government
                    has authorized him to make.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
